com.avaya.jtapi.tsapi

Interface LucentCallCenterAddress

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Address, CallCenterAddress, CallControlAddress, ITsapiAddress, LucentAddress, RouteAddress
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LucentACDManagerAddress, LucentV7ACDManagerAddress

    public interface LucentCallCenterAddress
extends LucentAddress
    When a Provider is bound to a Avaya switch, this interface may be used to access additional capabilities.

    Provides additional capability of adding CallListener on a CallCenterAddress with the option of the remain flag.

    • Method Detail

      • addCallListener

        void addCallListener(CallListener listener,
                     boolean remain)
              throws ResourceUnavailableException,
                     PrivilegeViolationException,
                     MethodNotSupportedException
        This method behaves similarly to Address.addCallListener(), with the following exceptions:

        • If remain is true, the listener remains on all Calls which come to this Address, for the lifetime of the Call.
        • If remain is false, this method behaves exactly the same as Address.addCallListener()

        If an application attempts to add an instance of an listener to the Address more than once, whether via the method or via the Address.addCallListener() method, only a single instance of an listener will be added. Repeated attempts to add an listener will silently fail, i.e. no exception is thrown.

        Post-Conditions:

        1. listener is an element of this.getCallListeners()
        2. listener is an element of Call.getListeners() for each Call associated with the Connections from this.getConnections()
        3. An array of snapshot events is reported to the listener for existing calls associated with this Address.

        Parameters:
        listener - The listener being added.
        remain - If true, the listener remains on the Call for the lifetime of the Call. If false, the listener uses the default behavior.
        Throws:
        MethodNotSupportedException - The Address is currently not observable.
        ResourceUnavailableException - The resource limit for the numbers of listeners has been exceeded.
        PrivilegeViolationException - The application does not have the proper authority to perform this type of observation.
        See Also:
        Address
